title: The Efficiency Expert
creator: Edgar Rice Burroughs
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Efficiency Expert by Edgar Rice Burroughs. Read by Delmar H. Dolbier Our hero, Jimmy Torrance, Jr., has a hard time finding suitable employment after a brilliant (athletically, at least) college career, despite all kinds of assistance from his friends in the underworld and the wealthy and sophisticated young woman with whom he falls in love. Set in contemporary America, mostly Chicago, this 1921 short novel is one of a handful of Burrough’s works that does not take us to a fantasy or an exotic setting. (Delmar H. Dolbier) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (142MB)
subject: librivox; audiobooks; fiction; 1921; Chicago; novel

reviews.reviewbody: real good all the way thru, constant interesting action

Great old fashioned story that's got it all - intrepid,  but not sappy sweet, hero; beautiful but treacherous woman; crooked boxing matches; whore with a heart of gold; honorable outlaw; despicable villains; and surprises and twists galore!  

The reader, Delmar H. Dolbier, does a GREAT job - though even I have to admit that his female voices are - ha ha - pathetic...it would be nice if he teamed up with a good female reader, and Librivox has some great ones.

But enough nitpicking, this is one of my top favorites and I'm listening to it all over again now.
reviews.reviewtitle: Terrific - one of my favorite Librivox books!
